metadata.name: Yellow House #102
metadata.description:
It is very easy to forget the beauty of the places we consume because they are available to us by nature.
The things we consume all our lives we find not so special.
It’s very hard to remember how special and valuable these things really are.

With this work, I will try to give sincere admiration and respect to my favorite place on the beach!

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 'f' to save .png with resolution = 4000px x 4000px

Created using p5js ,100% p5.js code and math.

@Mutart, April, 2022.

metadata.name: Fractured Cells #116
metadata.description:
Poisson disc sampling of a noise field masked to a shape, and then Voronoi tessellation. Rendered in hand-drawn lines.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 48 curated possible palettes
- 4 possible color distribution methods
- 3 possible shapes: one circle, random circles, circles distributed based on a quadtree 
- 1 to 3 levels of polygon smoothing
- polygon outlines
- polygon fill density and direction
- hand-drawn line roughness

Rare features
- 1 circle
- no polygon smoothing
- background polygons offset from foreground
- color distribution to have a "striped" appearance

metadata.name: Chaos Machine Part 1 #6
metadata.description:
This work of generative art explores the transitional and interactive spaces between determinism and randomness, between chaos and order, between human and computer, between surface and essence, and between artist and audience. 

Enjoy the art at the aesthetic level as it is generated by algorithm and chance, but also look deeper, explore, and see what u might discover.

Secondary royalties from this piece will be split with the original minter, and ownership of this piece will inform the access list for future related works.

metadata.name: Crystal Grove #19
metadata.description:
This project was inspired by molecular crystal growth.

While on a macro-level we can appreciate shapes and visuals as complete and solid, the microcosmos is built around complex structures that grow like roots and sometimes can appear messy, but are the pillar of what we can perceive with the naked eye.

Feel the groove of the Crystal Grove!

 [left-click to start a simple animation (if a crystal is present)]
[right-click to save (4096x4096)]

realized in JS

metadata.name: abstraction #12
metadata.description:
Diagrams of patterns on spheres, planets, fields, and platonic solids rendered isometrically. Ink on paper (on js).

Press DOWN to save an SVG suitable for plotting (or laser etching).
Press UP to save a 2400 x 2400 png. If you need a bigger image, zoom out and refresh, the canvas will fit the window.

Physics is fundamentally idealist. We search for simple rules from which the complexities of the universe emerge. But real systems are exceptionally complex, closed-form solutions are the exception. The deeper we dive into the fundamental nature of the universe, the less clear the rules become. Are the rules we've developed fundamental, or are they empirical approximations?

metadata.name: Sap song #48
metadata.description:
This audiovisual generative artwork proposes sonorous green forms that flow excessively. Frenetic arpeggios and populations of plants are emerging, organized in their own way. And the sap sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

II. “Recitativo libre”
III. “Coda hacia la raíz”

Original cello, marimba and music box samplers.

metadata.name: Computer fantasy #15
ProcGen Entomology #358
metadata.description:
Realtime 3D in-browser procedural generation of insect-like models, with a look reminiscent of vintage entomology illustrations.

The project is about the fact that insects are cool first and foremost.
This is also about nostalgia.

Everything is procedural except for the font. The exposed features only describe the most visible parts.

I wrote mord words, about where it came from, and some technical details on the procedural aspect at:
https://ulucode.com/projects/entomology/

GPU Required!

Interface : 
Space : show/hide menu
Mouse Left : Rotate
Mouse Right : Pan
Mouse Middle/Wheel : Zoom

Captures only work in Live mode.

metadata.name: Trianguland Series 4, Vol. 3 #9
metadata.description:
Trianguland is a very diverse kind of shape. It is based on a geometric construction of a triangle,
where vertices are connected using bezier curves, with the triangle's edge points being parameterized control points of the curves. The edginess determines the shape, e.g. forming special kind of loops.

Vol. 3 tweaks the edginess further to form a double-styled loop. Color overlay effects are based on P5's' difference blend mode. A motion turns the shape clockwise, modulating the edge parameters while giving it a thumping element.

A click in the canvas triggers a time-limited motion of the shape.
Press 'p' to start a continuous motion.
Pressing 's' saves the image as a PNG file.

Created by @aschmidt75 in 2022 using p5js.
https://linktr.ee/aschmidt75
